{
  "stem": "11882.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, Nuremberg-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Nuremberg was rubble.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Nuremberg was completely disrupted.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was the shell of a city, and our wonderful US Army superlatively managed most of this.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They took care of the logistics.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They brought all the food in, often powdered eggs and Spam and horrible army stuff.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But some-- and they hired all these people to come and manage the hotel and cook for us.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They had to organize everything.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The simplest things-- to get a car that would move and wasn't completely kaput, to make a telephone work, to telephone to all the outposts of Nuremberg, which were-- entire Europe was an outpost.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "There was no place in the world, excuse me, at that time but Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Washington was watching Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "England was watching Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "There was no Paris, no Italy-- they were pulling up from the war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And everybody who was anybody or who wasn't anybody was watching or in Nuremberg, or coming to visit Nuremberg, or writing about Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Walter Cronkite, later, Willy Brandt, many people who later were prime ministers and big British politicians, political figures, many famous Russians who later played a big role in Moscow were all in Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "As a girl in OSS said, when she heard I was going to Nuremberg-- oh, I'd like to go there, too, she said.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Everybody who is anybody is in Nuremberg-- OSS's attitude, you see.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And it was just the place to be and to watch.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Reporters had to get an assignment in Nuremberg.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And the world watched because we had been-- we had been in the paws of this man, Hitler.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We still thought he might be alive at that time.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
